verses.text_plain: When thou sittest to eat with a ruler, consider diligently what is before thee:
verses.verse_html: 1When thou sittest to eat with a ruler, consider diligently what is before thee:

verses.text_plain: And put a knife to thy throat, if thou be a man given to appetite.
verses.verse_html: 2And put a knife to thy throat, if thou be a man given to appetite.

verses.text_plain: Be not desirous of his dainties: for they are deceitful meat.
verses.verse_html: 3Be not desirous of his dainties: for they are deceitful meat.

verses.text_plain: Labour not to be rich: cease from thine own wisdom.
verses.verse_html: 4Labour not to be rich: cease from thine own wisdom.

verses.text_plain: Wilt thou set thine eyes upon that which is not? for riches certainly make themselves wings; they fly away as an eagle toward heaven.
verses.verse_html:
5Wilt thou set thine eyes upon that which is not? for riches certainly make themselves wings; they fly away as an eagle toward heaven. ▼
▼ set…: Heb. cause thine eyes to fly upon

footnotes.body_text: ▼ set…: Heb. cause thine eyes to fly upon
footnotes.body_html: ▼ set…: Heb. cause thine eyes to fly upon

verses.text_plain: Eat thou not the bread of him that hath an evil eye, neither desire thou his dainty meats:
verses.verse_html: 6Eat thou not the bread of him that hath an evil eye, neither desire thou his dainty meats:

verses.text_plain: For as he thinketh in his heart, so is he: Eat and drink, saith he to thee; but his heart is not with thee.
verses.verse_html: 7For as he thinketh in his heart, so is he: Eat and drink, saith he to thee; but his heart is not with thee.

tokens.text: he to thee; but his heart

verses.text_plain: The morsel which thou hast eaten shalt thou vomit up, and lose thy sweet words.
verses.verse_html: 8The morsel which thou hast eaten shalt thou vomit up, and lose thy sweet words.

verses.text_plain: Speak not in the ears of a fool: for he will despise the wisdom of thy words.
verses.verse_html: 9Speak not in the ears of a fool: for he will despise the wisdom of thy words.

verses.text_plain: Remove not the old landmark; and enter not into the fields of the fatherless:
verses.verse_html:
10Remove not the old landmark; and enter not into the fields of the fatherless: ▼
▼ landmark: or, bound

verses.text_plain: For their redeemer is mighty; he shall plead their cause with thee.
verses.verse_html: 11For their redeemer is mighty; he shall plead their cause with thee.

verses.text_plain: Apply thine heart unto instruction, and thine ears to the words of knowledge.
verses.verse_html: 12Apply thine heart unto instruction, and thine ears to the words of knowledge.

verses.text_plain: Withhold not correction from the child: for if thou beatest him with the rod, he shall not die.
verses.verse_html: 13Withhold not correction from the child: for if thou beatest him with the rod, he shall not die.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt beat him with the rod, and shalt deliver his soul from hell.
verses.verse_html: 14Thou shalt beat him with the rod, and shalt deliver his soul from hell.

verses.text_plain: My son, if thine heart be wise, my heart shall rejoice, even mine.
verses.verse_html:
15My son, if thine heart be wise, my heart shall rejoice, even mine. ▼
▼ even…: or, even I will rejoice

footnotes.body_text: ▼ even…: or, even I will rejoice
footnotes.body_html: ▼ even…: or, even I will rejoice

verses.text_plain: Yea, my reins shall rejoice, when thy lips speak right things.
verses.verse_html: 16Yea, my reins shall rejoice, when thy lips speak right things.

verses.text_plain: Let not thine heart envy sinners: but be thou in the fear of the Lord all the day long.
verses.verse_html: 17Let not thine heart envy sinners: but be thou in the fear of the Lord all the day long.

verses.text_plain: For surely there is an end; and thine expectation shall not be cut off.
verses.verse_html:
18For surely there is an end; and thine expectation shall not be cut off. ▼
▼ end: or, reward

verses.text_plain: Hear thou, my son, and be wise, and guide thine heart in the way.
verses.verse_html: 19Hear thou, my son, and be wise, and guide thine heart in the way.

verses.text_plain: Be not among winebibbers; among riotous eaters of flesh:
verses.verse_html:
20Be not among winebibbers; among riotous eaters of flesh: ▼
▼ of flesh: Heb. of their flesh

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of flesh: Heb. of their flesh
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of flesh: Heb. of their flesh

verses.text_plain: For the drunkard and the glutton shall come to poverty: and drowsiness shall clothe a man with rags.
verses.verse_html: 21For the drunkard and the glutton shall come to poverty: and drowsiness shall clothe a man with rags.

verses.text_plain: Hearken unto thy father that begat thee, and despise not thy mother when she is old.
verses.verse_html: 22Hearken unto thy father that begat thee, and despise not thy mother when she is old.

verses.text_plain: Buy the truth, and sell it not; also wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.
verses.verse_html: 23Buy the truth, and sell it not; also wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.

verses.text_plain: The father of the righteous shall greatly rejoice: and he that begetteth a wise child shall have joy of him.
verses.verse_html: 24The father of the righteous shall greatly rejoice: and he that begetteth a wise child shall have joy of him.

verses.text_plain: Thy father and thy mother shall be glad, and she that bare thee shall rejoice.
verses.verse_html: 25Thy father and thy mother shall be glad, and she that bare thee shall rejoice.

verses.text_plain: My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my ways.
verses.verse_html: 26My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my ways.

verses.text_plain: For a whore is a deep ditch; and a strange woman is a narrow pit.
verses.verse_html: 27For a whore is a deep ditch; and a strange woman is a narrow pit.

verses.text_plain: She also lieth in wait as for a prey, and increaseth the transgressors among men.
verses.verse_html:
28She also lieth in wait as for a prey, and increaseth the transgressors among men. ▼
▼ as for…: or, as a robber

footnotes.body_text: ▼ as for…: or, as a robber
footnotes.body_html: ▼ as for…: or, as a robber

verses.text_plain: Who hath woe? who hath sorrow? who hath contentions? who hath babbling? who hath wounds without cause? who hath redness of eyes?
verses.verse_html: 29Who hath woe? who hath sorrow? who hath contentions? who hath babbling? who hath wounds without cause? who hath redness of eyes?

verses.text_plain: They that tarry long at the wine; they that go to seek mixed wine.
verses.verse_html: 30They that tarry long at the wine; they that go to seek mixed wine.

verses.text_plain: Look not thou upon the wine when it is red, when it giveth his colour in the cup, when it moveth itself aright.
verses.verse_html: 31Look not thou upon the wine when it is red, when it giveth his colour in the cup, when it moveth itself aright.

verses.text_plain: At the last it biteth like a serpent, and stingeth like an adder.
verses.verse_html:
32At the last it biteth like a serpent, and stingeth like an adder. ▼
▼ an…: or, a cockatrice

footnotes.body_html: ▼ an…: or, a cockatrice

verses.text_plain: Thine eyes shall behold strange women, and thine heart shall utter perverse things.
verses.verse_html: 33Thine eyes shall behold strange women, and thine heart shall utter perverse things.

verses.text_plain: Yea, thou shalt be as he that lieth down in the midst of the sea, or as he that lieth upon the top of a mast.
verses.verse_html:
34Yea, thou shalt be as he that lieth down in the midst of the sea, or as he that lieth upon the top of a mast. ▼
▼ the midst…: Heb. the heart of the sea

tokens.text: Yea, thou shalt be as he that lieth down

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the midst…: Heb. the heart of the sea
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the midst…: Heb. the heart of the sea

verses.text_plain: They have stricken me, shalt thou say, and I was not sick; they have beaten me, and I felt it not: when shall I awake? I will seek it yet again.
verses.verse_html:
35They have stricken me, shalt thou say, and I was not sick; they have beaten me, and I felt it not: when shall I awake? I will seek it yet again. ▼
▼ I felt…: Heb. I knew it not

footnotes.body_text: ▼ I felt…: Heb. I knew it not
footnotes.body_html: ▼ I felt…: Heb. I knew it not
